      <div id="e-magazines" class="content-section">
        <h2>Instructions for remote access of e-magazines</h2>
        <p>You can read the newspapers and magazines available through PressReader in a library as well as outside the library using your own device.</p>
        <h3>PressReader</h3>
        <p>PressReader contains newspapers and magazines from around the world. You can read the publications either in your device’s browser or in the PressReader mobile app. To log in, 
        you need your Helmet library card number and PIN code.</p>
        <h4>Using PressReader in a web browser</h4>
        <p>Open the <a href="https://www.pressreader.com/catalog" target="_blank" aria-label="PressReader website. The link opens in a new window."> PressReader website</a>, 
        click Sign in and then choose the Library or group option. Next choosefrom the Select libraries list Library – Helmet libraries (offsite)
        and type in your library card number and PIN code. Wait a moment until a PressReader HotSpot window opens.</p>
        <p>You can browse the collection by tapping Select publication .Now you can browse the magazines according to country, language, category or publication type, or search by 
        title. Access the magazine by tapping on its cover.</p>
        
        <h4>Using PressReader via mobile app</h4>
        <p>Download thePressReader app from the App Store or Play store. If you have previously downloaded it, make sure you have the latest, updated version.</p>
        <p>Tap on Sign in, then tap Library or an icon resembling a library card. Choose from the Select libraries list Library – Helmet libraries (offsite) and enter your 
        library card number and PIN code. Wait a moment until a PressReader HotSpot window opens.</p>
        <p>After this, you can browse the selection, read magazines and newspapers as well as download them for offline use. The HotSpot must be active during downloading. 
        If the coffee cup symbol on the page is not green, activate the HotSpot in the app's settings.</p>
        <p>You can also download newspapers/magazines in the libraries’ wireless network in Helsinki and Espoo. This way you do not need to sign in to the PressReader app– 
        you just open the app and you are granted access automatically in the libraries’ wireless network.</p>
      </div>
      <div id="naxos" class="content-section">
        <h2>Audiobooks in different languages</h2>
        <p>In Naxos Spoken Word Library, you will find thousands of e-audiobooks. On offer are fiction and non-fiction titles mostly in English, including classics, memoirs, business 
        literature, and language courses.</p>
        <p>The service comprises mostly English audiobooks and radio plays as well as some French, German and Portuguese literature. There are several famous actors among the audiobook 
        readers. You can browse the collection by category, author or reader.</p>
        
        <h3>How to use Naxos Spoken Word Library</h3>
        <p>You can listen to NSWL e-audiobooks in a browser on your computer, tablet or smart phone. Log in with your library card number. Choose the book you want to listen to and start 
        listening straight away. You do not need to borrow or place holds on the books, they are all available all the time. You need to have internet access on while you are listening.</p>
        <p><a href="https://helsinkilib.naxosspokenwordlibrary.com" target="_blank" aria-label="Log in to Naxos Spoken Word Library. The link opens in a new window.">
        Log in to Naxos Spoken Word Library</a></p>
        <p>Up to 20 users can be logged in simultaneously to Naxos Spoken Word. Unfortunately, a small portion of the titles in Naxos Spoken Word Library cannot be accessed in Finland 
        due to copyright restrictions.</p>
        <p>On computers we recommend using the latest versions of Chrome, Firefox or Safari browsers. The browser must also support Flash. More detailed system requirements are available in 
        the <a href="https://helsinkilib.naxosspokenwordlibrary.com/faqs.asp" target="_blank" aria-label="Naxos Spoken Word Library’s FAQ section. The link opens in a new window.">
        Naxos Spoken Word Library’s FAQ section</a>.</p>
        
        <h3>Naxos Spoken Word also works on mobile devices</h3>
        <p>On iOS and Android devices, you can use the service via the NSWL application which you can get from your application store. You can also download e-audiobooks to the app for 
        listening offline. To use the apps, you need to create a personal user account. Do the following:</p>
        <ol class="list-bullets">
          <li>Go to the<a href="https://helsinkilib.naxosspokenwordlibrary.com"> Naxos Spoken World Library website.</a></li>
          <li>Log in with your Helmet library card number. Type the number without spaces.</li>
          <li>Click Create Student/member account link. Give the required data. You will get a confirmation by email, follow the instructions.</li>
          <li>Download the Naxos Spoken Word Library app to your mobile device.</li>
          <li>Log in to the app with the user account you created and enjoy the music.</li>
          <li>Remember to log outfrom the app when you are done with listening. The number of simultaneous users is limited.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>If you have not used the app for some time, signing in may fail. In that case, you will be sent an email to the email address you chose as your user name. Follow the 
        instructions in the email to reactivate the account.</p>
        
        <h3>Bookmark to continue listening later</h3>
        <p>When you have found a good e-audiobook from NSWL, you can choose to listen to the whole book (select all) or a chapter at a time. If you want to continue listening later, you 
        can bookmark the chapter by clicking the bookmark symbol. The bookmark is set to the beginning of the chapter you were just listening to.</p>
        <p>You can access the bookmarks you have created from the Bookmarks tab.</p><p>When you finish listening, log out from the service or close the NSWL app from your device’s cache. 
        In this way you enable other users to log in by freeing up the license for the next user.</p>
